==Latin==

===Adjective Suffix===
'''-anus''' ''m'', '''[[-ana]]''' ''f'', '''[[-anum]]''' ''n''
# of or pertaining to; adjective suffix appended to various words to turn them into adjectives.
#:Examples:
#::homo - humanus
#::anglicus - anglicanus
#::italia - italianus
#::Roma - Romanus

